==English==
===Pronunciation===
*/tʃəˈtʃɪŋ/, /tS@"tSIN/

===Etymology===
[[Imitative]] of the sound of a [[cash register]] when an amount is [[ring up|rung up]].  Popularized in 1992 by the movie [[w:Wayne's World|Wayne's World]] [[http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=uFD234eGNIUC&pg=PA211&lpg=PA211&dq=cha-ching&prev=http://books.google.com/books%3Fq%3Dcha-ching%26lr%3D%26start%3D10&sig=EhMu65HaBv0NssHk4gqMvo5CP_M 1]] and by a 1992 advertisement featuring [[w:Seth Green|Seth Green]] [[http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0001293/bio 2]].

===Interjection===
'''cha-ching'''
#(US, Australia) [[Score]]!; [[Wow]]!; said to [[celebrate]] something that has made or will make lots of [[money]]

===Verb===
'''cha-ching'''
#to make a cash register or slot machine [[noise]]; to make the noise of [[coin]]s [[falling]]

===Alternative forms===
*'''chaching''', '''ca-ching''' '''[[kerching]]''' (''primarily UK'')

